#using spark ML we are generating TFIDF vector which can be used to detect topics words from the data
from pyspark.ml.feature import CountVectorizer
from pyspark.ml.feature import IDF

stopWordList = stopwords.words('english')
#getting abstract text from dataset
text_col = 'Abstract'
abstract = df.select(text_col).filter(F.col(text_col).isNotNull()).toPandas().values
temp = []
for i in range(len(abstract)):
    words = abstract[i,0].lower().strip().split(" ")
    words = [word for word in words if not word in stopWordList] #remove stop words
    temp.append([i, words])
data = spark.createDataFrame(temp, ["id", "words"])
#get TFIDF vector from abstract
tfizer = CountVectorizer(inputCol='words',
                         outputCol='tf_features')
tf_model = tfizer.fit(data)
tf_result = tf_model.transform(data)
idfizer = IDF(inputCol='tf_features', outputCol='tf_idf_features')
idf_model = idfizer.fit(tf_result)
tfidf_result = idf_model.transform(tf_result)
tfidf_result.show()

#get topics words from trained LDA model
from pyspark.sql import types as T
vocab = tf_model.vocabulary
def get_words(token_list):
    return [vocab[token_id] for token_id in token_list]
udf_to_words = F.udf(get_words, T.ArrayType(T.StringType()))
num_top_words = 7
topics = lda_model.describeTopics(num_top_words).withColumn('topicWords', udf_to_words(F.col('termIndices')))
topics.select('topic', 'topicWords').show(truncate=100)

#now apply LSA on abstract to find more semantically similar words
from sklearn.decomposition import TruncatedSVD #using SVD will identify semnatically similar words
from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer
vec = CountVectorizer()
data = np.asarray(temp)[:,1]
for i in range(len(data)):
    data[i] = " ".join(data[i])
bow = vec.fit_transform(data.ravel())
svd = TruncatedSVD(n_components=4)#call SVD on abstract features
lsa = svd.fit_transform(bow)
similars = []
terms = vec.get_feature_names()
for i, comp in enumerate(svd.components_):#loop and get all semantically similar words
    terms_comp = zip(terms, comp)
    sorted_terms = sorted(terms_comp, key= lambda x:x[1], reverse=True)[:10]
    names = ""
    for t in sorted_terms:
        names += t[0]+" "
        similars.append([t[0], t[1]])
    print("Topic "+str(i)+" Semantically Similar words : "+names)    
similars = np.asarray(similars)

from itertools import chain
from nltk.corpus import wordnet #import NLTK package
for i, comp in enumerate(svd.components_):#loop and get all semantically similar words
    terms_comp = zip(terms, comp)
    sorted_terms = sorted(terms_comp, key= lambda x:x[1], reverse=True)[:10]
    for t in sorted_terms:
        synonyms = wordnet.synsets(t[0])#for each semnatic words get list of different words with same meaning
        word_list = set(chain.from_iterable([word.lemma_names() for word in synonyms]))
        if len(word_list) > 0:
            print(str(t[0])+" = "+str(word_list))
